+# Shared Supabase Migrations
+
+Apply these files in order:
+
+1. `001_shared_base.sql`
+2. `002_curriculum_render_namespace.sql`
+3. `003_lrsl_driller_namespace.sql`
+
+## Why These Migrations Keep Legacy Tables
+
+This cutover is compatibility-first.
+
+- `curriculum_render` still does direct Supabase `upsert()` calls against `answers` and `votes`.
+- `curriculum_render` also subscribes to Postgres changes on `answers`.
+- `lrsl-driller` still targets legacy table names from its Railway server.
+
+A hard rename of live tables would break those paths immediately. These migrations instead:
+
+- introduce `shared_users`
+- introduce `cr_answers`
+- expose `cr_*` and `drill_*` namespace relations
+- keep legacy tables available during transition
+- tighten driller-side access so shared anon reads do not expose driller data
+
+## Verification
+
+Run the dry run first against a linked test project:
+
+```bash
+supabase db push --linked --dry-run
+```
+
+Then verify the shared auth surface with the project anon key:
+
+```bash
+curl "https://your-shared-project.supabase.co/rest/v1/shared_users?select=username,real_name,user_type" ^
+  -H "apikey: $ANON_KEY"
+```
